Netizen contribution December 13th WeChat circulated a picture showing that the Ministry of Public Security put forward the "eight must not happen again" work requirements, including: 
1. No major risks involving political stability; 
2. No extreme violent incidents such as individual driving collisions and revenge on society; 
3. No large-scale stampede accidents; 
4. No non-organized, large-scale gatherings such as "night riding"; 
5. No labeling incidents such as "white paper movement" and so-called mourning, tomb sweeping and other activities; 
6. No "rights protection" gatherings and other mass incidents caused by malicious wage arrears, layoffs, etc.; 
7. No major gun-related and explosive-related crimes, and the bottom line of no violent terrorist incidents must be maintained; 
8. No late reporting, underreporting, false reporting or concealment, and resolutely prevent small problems from dragging down and exploding.

On December 18, Chaoyang City, Liaoning Province adjusted the old-age allowance policy for the elderly: 
100 yuan per month for low-income elderly people aged 80 to 89; 
30 yuan per month for other elderly people aged 80 to 89; 
200 yuan per month for elderly people aged 90 to 99; 
1,000 yuan per month for elderly people over 100 years old.
